The most challenging monster in the *Dungeons & Dragons 5th Edition Monster Manual* is widely considered to be the **Tarrasque**.

\boxed{B}

Its **CR 30** (highest in the book) and devastating multiattack make it nearly unstoppable for most parties, even at high levels. While a beholder or lich can be deadly, the Tarrasque’s raw power and sheer presence make it the ultimate boss-level threat.
